Text: Power DB Field RequirementsNonPrivilegedpst Chris Attached is the spreadsheet shared with KPMG Feel free to add anything else needed for settlement One area that we thought you could provided a lot of insight to is the upperlower band and parameters needed for to figure these calculations hourly daily monthly annually etc Call if you have any questions Please forward back with any changes you might make Thanks Steve x

CSC TerminologyNonPrivilegedpst Chris do you know what the following coding means per CSC invoicing file Active Submitted Cancelled Closed Deactive Pending I am trying to reconcile what we believe the total deal population is for California Utilities PGE SoCal and SDGE Steve

Update InformationNonPrivilegedpst Attached is a spreadsheet created by KPMG with some results from CSC data and RPS testing done on California This is just for your information Do you have any idea what percentage of contracts will have a band consumption I am trying to understand your personnel needs to accomplish your objectives You can give me a call to discuss or just respond via email Thanks Steve

Update meetingNonPrivilegedpst Have you heard if the update meeting was cancelled for this week or will be rescheduled If there still is a meeting this week we need to finish the update slides Did you get with Paige Grumulaitis or are you going to reschedule Let me know when you get a chance Steve x

Update slideNonPrivilegedpst Attached is the update slides for Tuesday Chris as you will see Phase needs some bullet point description If you dont have a chance to fill in I will come up with something You can reach me at x Thanks

Field validationsNonPrivilegedpst Attached is the same spreadsheet that lists out plus information fields needed for the power process I have taken a first cut at what we specifically want validated by KPMG I have made these fields red or if you print you will see a small x to the left of the field name Please review and let me know if there are other fileds that should be validated in this process or if I have highlighted fields that do not need to be validated We can discuss this afternoon Steve x

RPS DumpNonPrivilegedpst I was reviewing the data dump request from Scott to Todd Taylor and wondered if this was sufficient for the settlement side of this project We have only requested usage for and I would believe that we would need usage information for to Are we getting this from another source Should we stop the current request and modify or can we add this to the database with the next RPS dump request Any thoughts would be appreciated Steve x
